    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Farmers of Spokane county who\nrecall the vigorous and honorable\nfight made in their behalf and\nagainst the railroads by Warren w.\nTolman for his railroad rate bill.\nwill be glad to vote for the accom-\nplished lawyer and student of public\nmatters for the dignified office of\njustice of the supreme court. The\nfact that the republicans have\nstolen Mr.. Tolman's ideas and in\ncorporated the best of them in the\npresent railroad commission law,\ndetracts in no degree from Mr.. Toll\nmans popularity in eastern Wash\nington, or in the entire state, for\nthat matter."
    }
  ]
